					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">You mean why the waveform in your screenshot appears to jump back a few phase steps, rather than forward by a few as one would expect? No idea on that. Or perhaps why it occurs at different rates on different emulators? Granularity of them running their emulated APU, or possibly different initial timing or timing accuracy of the emulator in general. Occurrence would be a complex combination of things so that slight changes in accuracy would have a big effect on the pattern of occurrence (e.g. it's chaotic).</div>

